info.description: # trieres This is a python module enabling the remote execution of accelerated functions on the [cloudFPGA platform](https://www.zurich.ibm.com/cci/cloudFPGA/). ## Workflow to upload a new package at pypi ``` git clone --depth 1 --recursive git@github.com:cloudFPGA/trieres.git cd trieres make env source venv/bin/activate make dist make upload ``` ## Notes Optionally to crate a new package by using the latest cFp_Zoo : ``` git clone --depth 1 --recursive git@github.com:cloudFPGA/trieres.git cd trieres make env source venv/bin/activate cd trieres/cFp_Zoo git pull make dist make upload ```
info.name: trieres
info.summary: A cloud-native python library for domain-specific cloud FPGAs.
